00:00:04.839 --> 00:00:05.099
this going to show how to slip stitch and
attach a new color

00:00:05.099 --> 00:00:12.099
i want to start with a slip knot

00:00:18.260 --> 00:00:25.260
i take this yarn which is the tail

00:00:28.250 --> 00:00:28.500
wrap it over the top

00:00:28.250 --> 00:00:28.500
i take this loop

00:00:28.250 --> 00:00:28.500
and wrap it over the main portion of my yarn

00:00:28.480 --> 00:00:28.730
insert the hook underneath

00:00:28.510 --> 00:00:28.760
and then on top of this strand here

00:00:28.570 --> 00:00:28.820
this creates my slip knot

00:00:28.600 --> 00:00:30.529
i will use s slip knot and slip stitch combination
to attach new colors of yarn

00:00:30.529 --> 00:00:33.899
now attach the new color

00:00:33.899 --> 00:00:38.640
in any loop with a slip stitch

00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:45.640
i am attaching my yarn between the stitches
here on round one

00:00:47.520 --> 00:00:53.559
now we want to attach the yarn

00:00:53.559 --> 00:01:00.559
right here in the toe top

00:01:07.719 --> 00:01:17.560
attach the new color of yarn

00:01:17.560 --> 00:01:20.170
with a slip knot to your crochet hook

00:01:20.170 --> 00:01:23.020
insert the crochet hook

00:01:23.020 --> 00:01:27.310
through the top of the stitch

00:01:27.310 --> 00:01:29.099
wrap the yarn over your crochet hook

00:01:29.099 --> 00:01:32.099
pull it through the stitch

00:01:32.099 --> 00:01:36.299
and pull it through the slip knot

00:01:36.299 --> 00:01:39.399
to complete attaching your new color of yarn

